# purrphp/collection — extension patterns

## Class hierarchy

```
AbstractCollection
├── AbstractList                   — ordered list (array_values, numeric keys)
│   ├── AbstractSet                — deduplicates values on construction
│   ├── ...List / ...NotEmptyList
│   └── AbstractMutableList        — extends AbstractList, ArrayAccess + in-place mutation
└── AbstractMap                    — associative map (string/int keys)
    └── AbstractMutableMap         — mutable map (ArrayAccess)
```

**When to use which:**
- `AbstractList` — ordered sequence, duplicates allowed
- `AbstractSet` — ordered sequence of **unique** values (extends `AbstractList`, order is preserved)
- `AbstractMap` — key → value, immutable
- `AbstractMutableList` — ordered sequence with in-place mutation and `ArrayAccess`
- `AbstractMutableMap` — key → value with in-place mutation and `ArrayAccess`

> There is no `AbstractMutableSet`. Implement mutable sets by extending your concrete mutable list and re-checking uniqueness after each mutation. See `IntMutableSet` as a reference.

## Creating a new collection

### Immutable List

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractList<MyType> */
class MyTypeList extends AbstractList
{
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        parent::__construct($items);
    }

    protected function filterUniqValues(array $items): array
    {
        return array_unique($items); // or custom logic for objects
    }
}
```

### NotEmpty variant

```php
class MyTypeNotEmptyList extends MyTypeList
{
    /** @throws \Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException */
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        if (!$items) {
            throw new \Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException('Items are empty');
        }
        parent::__construct(...$items);
    }
}
```

### Immutable Set

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractSet<MyType> */
class MyTypeSet extends AbstractSet
{
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        parent::__construct($items);
    }

    protected function filterUniqValues(array $items): array
    {
        $seen   = [];
        $result = [];

        foreach ($items as $item) {
            $key = $item->getId(); // domain-specific uniqueness criterion
            if (!isset($seen[$key])) {
                $seen[$key] = true;
                $result[]   = $item;
            }
        }

        return $result;
    }
}
```

### Immutable Map

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractMap<MyType> */
class MyTypeMap extends AbstractMap
{
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        parent::__construct($items);
    }

    protected function filterUniqValues(array $items): array
    {
        return array_unique($items);
    }
}
```

### Mutable List

Mutable variants require `ensureType()` to validate values on every write (offsetSet, insert, prepend, etc.):

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractMutableList<MyType> */
class MyTypeMutableList extends AbstractMutableList
{
    public function __construct(MyType ...$items)
    {
        parent::__construct($items);
    }

    protected function ensureType(mixed $value): void
    {
        if (!$value instanceof MyType) {
            throw new \Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentTypeException(
                type: get_debug_type($value),
                expects: MyType::class,
            );
        }
    }

    protected function filterUniqValues(array $items): array
    {
        return array_unique($items);
    }
}
```

## Immutability

All methods returning `static` must create a **new instance**:

```php
// ✅ Correct
return new static(...$filteredItems);

// ❌ Incorrect — mutates $this->collection
$this->collection = $filteredItems;
```

## Psalm / PHPStan annotations (required)

```php
/** @template-extends AbstractList<MyType> */         // List, Set
/** @template-extends AbstractSet<MyType> */          // Set
/** @template-extends AbstractMap<MyType> */          // Map (value type only)
/** @template-extends AbstractMutableList<MyType> */  // MutableList
/** @template-implements CollectionInterface<MyType> */ // on custom interfaces
```

## filterUniqValues

`filterUniqValues(array $items): array` is abstract in `AbstractCollection` and **must be implemented** in every concrete class.

- For **scalars**: delegate to `array_unique($items)`.
- For **objects**: iterate with `foreach` and track seen keys via a `$seen` map; collect results in a sequential `$result` array.

The method is called in the `AbstractSet` constructor and by `unique()` on all collections. Always return a plain sequential array (list-safe).

## Exceptions

Use `Purr\Collection\Exception\InvalidArgumentException` (extends `\InvalidArgumentException`).
